The evt300 radar driver was originally written by Paul Kretz, and
ported to Linux by Sue Dickey and John Spring.  

January 24 2008 -- version in this directory has had mods to evt300.h
from version in the cabinet in order to run standalone, and some clean up.
Functionality for writing radar files in the format that researchers
like Ching-yao and Xiao-yun have used in the past (formerly written
by wrfiles) has been added. A stub has been put in for export to mysql.
It compiles but has not yet been tested. Sue 

July 25, 2008 -- evt300 executable using the library has been in use
since May 2008 in the RFS intersection, with no reported problems and
correct operation of the IDS demo. 
